Three staged approach to the surgical management of renal cell carcinoma extending into the right atrium. Case report.
 Left renal cell carcinoma extending into the right atrium was treated by angioinfarction, removal of right atrial tumour using cardiopulmonary bypass and ten days later abdominal radical nephrectomy and inferior vena cava thrombectomy.
 Twenty four months later the patient remains well with no evidence of tumour recurrence.
